responseFromOwnerText: Thanks so much for such a lovely review! Let us know when you're popping back in, we would love to see you again soon
text:
Lovely eatery near Streatham Hill and really does deliver on all fronts.

Service and atmosphere are first rate and a pleasant change to most of the offerings in this area.

The menu is small but almost everything on it is excellent. We had the Arrabiata pasta and the shrimp pasta, and both were fantastic. They also have smaller bites for the "not too hungry brigade".

Dessert was the white chocolate Mousse and the stick toffee pudding (a waitress recommendation), and these were both virtually perfect.

Lunch for 2 came to £65 with tip.

Perhaps the easiest recommendation I have given for this part of town and it's a must visit if you are in the area and fancy a quick bite or something more substantial.

address: 5 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1EF, United Kingdom
name: Naomi
responseFromOwnerText: So sorry to see the 2 stars, please do get in touch directly on hello@sw16barandkitchen.com
text:
I visited last week for date night & the food was great but the service was so poor.

We waited 50 minutes for our roasts, & I brought it to their attention when my boyfriend noticed someone who came after us got their food before. Both our meals then came cold & without Yorkshire puddings until I reminded them it says it comes with it on the menu. We sent our plates back & waited another 10 or so minutes

This time around the meals were great, roast potatoes were a little bit on the hard side but other than that everything was delicious. I had the celeriac roast, I’ve not tried celeriac before but I loved it! & my boyfriend enjoyed his meal as well

We got our meals on the house because of the wait/cold food, but it’s a shame as I saw such great reviews before I booked but I guess they were just having a bad day

I would try this place again though because the roasts were really tasty, just hoping the service will be 10 times better next time..
title: SW16 Bar & Kitchen

name: Lana
responseFromOwnerText: Thanks for your feedback, sorry to read this, please do get in touch with us directly hello@sw16barandkitchen.com
text:
If it wasn't for our fabulous waiter Nick I am unsure if I would've stayed past the starter at SW16 for dinner.
I've been before and loved it but this time was disappointing.

The crab dumpling was not what we expected. I have no idea why it is called a dumpling, because it has never met one. There is a thimble of crab and the "dumpling" is a thinly shaven beetroot.  Do not order, if hungry, in fact at all.
Beef tartar starter was nice.

The main was delicious but I had two small pieces of beef in the tagliatelle. My date had the crab linguine and there was scarcely any crab.
Then to top it off it was an expensive meal.
I live in Streatham not Soho, I was honestly surprised.

Unfortunately he had to order food on the way home as the meal was not enough.

Nick, thank you for being hospitable. You were the highlight of the evening.

name: rebecca chesney
responseFromOwnerText: Hi Rebecca, I'm so sorry to read this, please do get in touch with us directly hello@sw16barandkitchen.com
text:
Really disappointing venue. Food and service both incredibly poor, portion sizes very small also.
We were advised by the staff that they do not have a kids menu but can adapt dishes. We had a 3 & 6 year old with us; ordered the pancakes for them and asked for a kids portion. Was advised by staff that they couldn’t adapt these for the kids but that the portions weren’t that big. Pancakes were disgracefully small, 2 tiny pancakes, our 6 year old finished them and was still
Hungry after - it is not an adult portion.
Two of us ordered the seafood linguine and the other the chicken salad. The ‘linguine’ was spaghetti, a very poor sauce with minimal seafood. Admittedly I asked for no squid, however, my portion had a total of 2 overcooked and chewy prawns and 3 mussels, my mums was similar (this dish costs £14.50).
The salad that was ordered was covered in a sauce that was a bit off with a very small amount of very bland chicken, so my sister couldn’t finish it as it was so tasteless.
The service was incredibly slow, we had to ask for the bill twice before someone brought it.
I advised the staff of the poor food quality and service and the only thing offered from them was to change some of the food (this is 20 minutes after we finished eating), they did not offer any compensation or even a chat with the manager, nothing.
Overall an incredibly disappointing experience, would definitely not go back here and would not recommend. We all left hungry and felt it was a complete waste of money.
title: SW16 Bar & Kitchen

name: A B
responseFromOwnerText: So sorry to read this, please do get in touch with us directly on hello@sw16barandkitchen.com
text: After seeing so many good reviews, me and my partner decided to try this place out. The food was good, no complaints. We both work in hospitality, and are the first to understand if anything is lacking. However, the restaurant was quiet, and the brunette who served us was not the nicest. She was very grumpy, and we felt that we had done something personal to her. We were not paid attention to at all, ordered things that never came, waited ages to pay for the bill until we had to stand up and ask (which is always uncomfortable). Eating out nowadays, we would not expect to be served someone that clearly did not want to be there, which again we understand, but were made to feel like it was our fault that she was working. We gave the benefit of the doubt and assumed it was just a bad day, but regardless, surely we weren’t the cause of that. This is one of the unfortunate occasions in which we would not be returning because of the  experience and not the food.

text:
The Sunday roast chicken was a little too pale for me but well cooked just needed more seasoning and more colour. More potatoes please, I would of loved more potatoes but tasted very nice. Really nice atmosphere, very helpful team and very welcoming.

The only thing is from the entrance of the restaurant there’s a ramp which was helpful but then went you actually get inside the restaurant, there’s another very big step with no wheelchair access over that big step, so was a little difficult with my pushchair, but just thinking also for wheelchair users that do not want to stay outside for their meals and drinks it would’ve difficult (outside seating areas)

Really nice bathroom and changing area for babies (bin please should be in the cubicle too, makes life easier). The setup of the restaurant was nice and lots of space. Very nice and calm ambiance. I would definitely come back again without a pushchair

name: Luke
responseFromOwnerText:
Hi Luke

Thanks so much for the review, great to read the awesome feedback! Please note that the service charge goes directly to our staff
text:
Popped in for a quick spot of brunch on Saturday. The place has a nice ambience and the waiter was very friendly although it took a while for us to be acknowledged at the door.

We ordered the short rib benedict, salmon royale and polenta chips to share, as well as a coffee each. The food came quickly and all of the dishes tasted great. Short rib benedict was packed with flavour with a good hit of spice from the nduja hollandaise, and the salmon royale had a good serving of salmon and a delicious black garlic aioli. The polenta fries were exceptional, served with a delicious miso mayo. The portions were quite small though, both dishes served with only a single poached egg neither of which had a runny yolk. I feel that SW16 Kitchen has the potential to compete with some of the really great bougie brunch places in South London, but getting a poached egg right needs to be top if the agenda!

We did really enjoy the food but it is quite expensive, our bill came to over £40 in the end. Unfortunately SW16 has adopted the increasingly-common-in-London practice of adding on an automatic 12.5% service charge, which is a bit excessive for a 30 minute stop for brunch.
title: SW16 Bar & Kitchen

Hi William,

text:
Not sure if SW16 Bar & Kitchen was what I expected when we chose to visit. Now, this may sound like the start to a bad review, but this was anything but. As it happens, the crew delivered the most wonderful of experiences for us.

The cocktails were exceptional, and the brunch was everything and more.

I actually found myself accidentally walking towards the kitchen, in hopes of stealing the recipe for their pulled beef Benedict (I found the toilet eventually).

I can honestly say, without the slightest hesitation, that you should visit SW16 bar and kitchen as soon as you can. At least for anyone out there with similar sensibilities to us.

If you do choose to drink or eat there, I can say with every confidence, you will be starting your weekend in the best possible way.

Special thanks to Will and Jenni for making us feel so at home over the last two weekends, and hopefully we will see you soon.

text:
Not usually one to write negative reviews, but this place is a disappointing restaurant disguised behind an Instagrammably Clapham-ish facade.
A happy hour menu the serving staff were apparently unaware of. A table with a lamp that somehow managed to blind one of us whichever way we positioned it. 'Buratta' salad which turned up as a watery spoonful of curds atop some leaves. 'Disco bread' which is frankly an inedibly salty, crispy offence to bread itself that left us blaming ourselves for not asking what disco bread is in the first place.
Everything about this restaurant screams 'post it on the gram' rather than 'we care about good food and service'.
Didn't get any pasta, so maybe that's where all the chefs' energy goes. Would just love to see a bit more care and soul in these dishes.

name: London Double Trouble
text:
A lovely setting! Would highly recommend for a few reasons.

When arriving you have a choice to either sit down for a drink or have a table to eat from the food menu. We arrived here after going to the cinema around 5pm on a Saturday. Which is more of a quiet slot, as the hour went by the evening crowds were arriving which had a mix of people, families, friend gatherings and couples.

Guessing from the popularity of it to book, the location is on the high street and very close to Streatham Hill Station which leads you east towards Crystal Place or West to Balham and up to Victoria so it's a good spot if have further plans or coming from these locations.

Streatham we feel can be under rated but this place was a good example of why to visit and support businesses like this.

We will be coming again and with some pictures attached.

Solid A*****

LDT x
